abstract_eng:
One of the pressing problems in water sector is the issues of water quality and supply to Ulaanbaatar city in which nearly ½ of Mongolian population resides. Through determining recharge contribution of each sources, and understanding dynamics of surface and groundwater interaction, knowledge based management decisions can be made. Though, to the best of our knowledge, there is only one published study using isotopic analysis for identification of sources of alluvial ground water of Tuul River basin and interaction between ground and surface water. According to this study, northern tributaries and ground water from northern part of Ulaanbaatar contributes up to 54% and winter precipitation contributes up to 12% of alluvial ground water of Tuul River Basin, in addition to recharge contribution of Tuul River. Due to climate change and thawing of permafrost, various changes such as decrease in ground water supply, increase in base flow, changes in quality have been observed. Similar phenomena such as increase in thaw depth, increase in nitrate and ammonia in water supply wells have been observed in Ulaanbaatar area. This indicates that changes in permafrost, and soil pollution in gerhoroolol, underlain by discontinuous permafrost zone, can affect ground supply and quality. However, we have not encountered a study that aimed to determine recharge contributions of each sources and define the role of permafrost in hydrological cycle. 
The result of the project will be described dynamics of surface and groundwater interaction in the discontinuous permafrost region of the Tuul river basin.  Expected outcomes of the project will be defined followings: 
a)	Understanding of recharge contributions of each sources  (rainfall, snowmelt, surface water), base flow dynamics  in permafrost area;
b)	Defined role  of  permafrost, underlain the northern tributaries of the Tuul river basin;
c)	Policy relevant recommendation on land and climate change impacts on surface and groundwater in the permafrost region;
d)	Workshops and trainings of young hydrological researchers on advanced methods of hydrology, particularly in models of isotope analysis;
e)	At least onearticle to peer reviewed international journal
The overall result will be a key understanding of surface water reaction to the permafrost region of Mongolia.

The purpose of this project is 1. To do research on radical theory of rings and produce new results; 2. To do research on the model of Paul-Fierts;
3. To do research on the singular points and asymptote of quartics and produce new results; 4. To do research with other branches of mathematics and use its application in various fields; 5. To promote research of the other branches of mathematics.
During this project, we will do research mainly on radical theory of rings, algebraic geometry, analysis.

abstract_mn:
Энэхүү төслийн зорилго нь Монгол улсад (зорилтот бүлэг: залуучуудад) ажил мэргэжлийн чиг баримжаа олгох үйлчилгээг илүү мэргэжлийн түвшинд хүргэхэд хувь нэмэр ээ оруулахад оршино; Монгол улс нь эдийн засгийн болон улс төрийн шилжилтийн үйл явцад байгаа бөгөөд ажил мэргэжлийн чиг баримжаа олгох чиглэлээр хөгжлийн нотлогдсон хэрэгцээ байна. Төвлөрөх асуудал:  
a.	Монгол улсад залуучуудын ажил мэргэжлийн чиг баримжаа олгох үйл ажиллагааны өнөөгийн практик болон ирээдүйн сорилуудыг тодорхойлох (одоогийн-нөхцөл байдал); 
b.	Мэргэжил сонголттой холбоотой оношилгооны аргуудыг боловсруулах, үнэлэх; 
c.	Залуучуудад АМЧБО тогтолцооны загвар боловсруулах; 
d.	“Залуучуудад АМЧБОТ”-ны загварыг боловсруулж, түүнийг хэрэгжүүлэхэд чиглэсэн бодлогын зөвлөмжийг боловсруулах (байвал зохих-нөхцөл байдал);
e.	Тархаах (нийтлэл, эрдэм шинжилгээний хурал гэх мэт);
f.	ЕРАЗМУС+ (ERASMUS+) хөтөлбөрт чадавхийг бэхжүүлэх (capacity building) чиглэлээр төслийн өргөдөл гаргах

abstract_eng:
Projekt-Output
Ziel des Projektes ist es, einen Beitrag zur Professionalisierung der Berufsberatung (Zielgruppe: Jugendliche) in der Mongolei zu leisten; in einem Land, dass sich in einem wirtschaftlichen und politischen Transformationsprozess befindet und einen evidenten Entwicklungsbedarf in der beruflichen Beratung aufweist. Der Fokus liegt auf der 
a.	Feststellung der gegenwärtigen Praxis und der künftigen Herausforderungen im Bereich der beruflichen Beratung für Jugendliche in der Mongolei (Ist-Zustand); 
b.	Entwicklung und Evaluierung von Diagnoseverfahren bei der Berufswahl; 
c.	Entwicklung eines Modells für die berufliche Beratung von Jugendlichen; 
d.	Erarbeitung von Politikempfehlungen zur Entwicklung und Implementierung eines System-Modells zur beruflichen Beratung von Jugendlichen in der Mongolei (Soll-Zustand);
e.	Dissemination (Publikationen, Fachkonferenzen etc.);
f.	 Erasmus+ Antrag im Bereich Capacity Building

abstract_mn:
Цар тахал Ковид-19-с Монголын аялал жуулчлалын салбарт учруулж буй эдийн засгийн нөлөөллийг судалж, тулгамдаж буй асуудлуудыг илрүүлэх, хамаарлыг шинжлэн асуудлыг шийдвэрлэх үндсийг тодорхойлов. Энэ хүрээнд аялал жуулчлалын тур оператор байгууллагуудын удирдах албан хаагчдыг судалгаанд хамруулж, цар тахлын үеийн бизнесийн нөхцөл байдал, тэдний өөрсдийн болоод засгийн газраас авч хэрэгжүүлж буй арга хэмжээг хэрхэн үнэлж байгаа болон цаашид аялал жуулчлалыг салбарыг хэрхэн сэргээх талаарх саналыг судлав. Энэ хүрээнд дараах зорилтуудыг биелүүлэв. Үүнд:
§ Монгол улсын дотоодын болоод олон улсын аялал жуулчлалын зах зээлд Ковид-19 цар тахлаас учруулж буй эдийн засгийн нөлөөг тооцоолов;
§ Улмаар аялал жуулчлалын салбарын бүрдэл хэсэг болох инбаунд, аутбаунд тур операторуудад нөлөөлж буй нөлөөллийн цар хэмжээг тодруулав;
§ Тус салбарын бизнес эрхлэгчид, удирдах ажилтнууд, ажиллагсад засгийн газраас бодлогын ямар шийдэл хүлээж байгааг тоймлов.

abstract_eng:
Present study explored the economic impact of Covid-19 pandemic on the Mongolian tourism sector, identified  challenges, and analyzed the interrelationships to identify solutions.
In this context, a survey research conducted covering tour operators to assess the business situation during the pandemic, how they assess themselves and the measures taken by the government, and how to revitalize the tourism sector in the future. In this context, the following objectives have been met. These include:
§ Estimated of the economic impact of Covid-19 pandemic on Mongolia's domestic and international tourism markets;
§ Further, the extent of the impact on inbound and outbound tour operators, which are components of the tourism industry, was clarified;
§ Businesses, executives and employees in the sector provided an overview of what policy decisions expected from the government of Mongolia.

Scope of Work:
i)	Conduct a research study on political finance in Mongolia and international good practices
•	Review of political finance regulations and mechanisms that had been used in Mongolia and their outcomes in practice, and identify main issues to be resolved, through desk review and interviews and discussions with relevant stakeholders;
•	Review previous research studies on political finance in Mongolia;
•	Review recent and latest international practices of legal regulations of political finance, and devise key lessons to be learned for Mongolia, especially from the perspective of implications for gender equality in politics and women’s empowerment;
•	Prepare research report as well as PPP slides for obtaining feedback from diverse groups of stakeholders, including women in politics, and those working at sub-national level;
ii)	Draft a concept note for developing a draft law on political financing
•	Develop a concept note based on the findings of the research and in consultation with the key stakeholders;  
•	Prepare PPPs, relevant info graphics and a summary of the proposed draft law on political finance, including how the proposed concept would enable gender equality in politics and decision-making;
•	Present the draft report and key proposals at stakeholder consultative meetings, present the concept and the summary of the proposed legislative provisions at consultations/discussions at the national and subnational levels, and diverse groups of stakeholders, including women’s caucus in the parliament, and document the feedback received by each of the groups;
•	Update the concept based on the feedback from the stakeholders;
iii) Provide support to drafting of the legal text, in consultation with stakeholders. 
•	Assist in drafting the legal text upon consultation with the SCSS and other key stakeholders;
•	Assist in refining the draft law based on consultations;
•	Prepare a summary for general public, including explanation how the proposed law would enable gender equality;

abstract_mn:
Энэхүү үнэлгээний ажлын гол зорилго нь Үндэсний их баяр наадмын тухай хуулийн төслийн хэм хэмжээнд (ихэнх зүйл, хэсэг, заалт)-д тодорхой шалгуур үзүүлэлтийн дагуу дүн шинжилгээ хийх, үр нөлөөг тооцож, давхардал, хийдэл, зөрчлийг арилгах, хуулийн зохицуулалтыг ойлгомжтой, хэрэгжихэд хууль хоорондын зөрчилдөөн үүсэхгүй байдлаар боловсруулах, хуулийн төслийн чанарыг сайжруулахад оршино. 
Үндэсний их баяр наадам нь Монгол Улсын тусгаар тогтнол, бүрэн эрхт байдлыг илэрхийлж уламжлалт урлаг, спорт, соёлын олон төрөл зүлийг багтаасан аялал жуулчлалын гол арга хэмжээ болон хөгжиж байна. 
Хүчин төгөлдөр үйлчилж байгаа Үндэсний их баяр наадмын тухай хуулийн зорилт нь Үндэсний их баяр наадмыг улс орон даяар тэмдэглэн өнгөрүүлэхтэй холбогдсон харилцааг зохицуулахад оршиж байгаа бөгөөд улс, аймаг, нийслэл, сумын баяр наадмыг зохион байгуулах, бөх, хурдан морины уяач, сурын харваачид цол, чимэг олгох, тэдний эрх үүрэг, допингийн эсрэг үйл ажиллагаа, хариуцлагын тогтолцоотой холбоотой эрх зүйн хэм хэмжээ бүрдэхэд чухал ач холбогдолтой алхам болсон.
Хэдийгээр хүчин төгөлдөр үйлчилж байгаа Үндэсний их баяр наадмын тухай хууль байгаа хэдий ч сүүлийн жилүүдэд үндэсний бөхийн барилдаан, үндэсний хурдан морьдын уралдаан тойрсон маргаантай, ээдрээтэй асуудлууд гарч, баяр наадмын зохион байгуулалтад тодорхой бэрхшээл учруулах болсон. Үүнтэй холбогдуулж Хууль зүй, дотоод хэргийн яамнаас Үндэсний их баяр наадмын тухай хуулийн шинэчилсэн найруулгын хуулийн төсөл /цаашид “хуулийн төсөл” гэх/-ийг боловсруулсан тул тус төсөлд Хууль тогтоомжийн тухай хуульд заасан шаардлагын дагуу төслийн үр нөлөөний судалгааг “Хуулийн төслийн үр нөлөө үнэлэх аргачлал”  /цаашид “аргачлал” гэх/-д заасны дагуу дараах үе шаттайгаар хийлээ:
1.Шалгуур үзүүлэлтийг сонгох;
	2.Хуулийн төслөөс үр нөлөө үнэлэх хэсгээ тогтоох;
3.Урьдчилан сонгосон шалгуур үзүүлэлтэд тохирох шалгах хэрэгслийн дагуу төслийн үр нөлөөг үнэлэх;
	4. Үр дүнг үнэлэх, зөвлөмж өгөх.

abstract_eng:
The main purpose of this evaluation is to analyze the norms (most articles, sections, provisions) of the draft law on the National Naadam Festival in accordance with certain criteria, calculate the impact, eliminate duplications, gaps and violations, and make the legal regulations clear and enforceable. to improve the quality of the draft law so that there is no conflict between them.
The National Naadam Festival is developing into a major tourism event that embodies Mongolia's independence and sovereignty and includes a variety of traditional arts, sports and cultural events.The purpose of the current Law on the National Naadam Festival is to regulate relations related to the celebration of the National Naadam throughout the country. It is an important step in the development of legal norms related to the issuance, their rights and responsibilities, anti-doping activities and accountability systems.Despite the current Law on the National Naadam Festival, in recent years there have been controversial issues surrounding national wrestling and national equestrian events, which have created certain difficulties for the organization of the Naadam. In this regard, the Ministry of Justice and Home Affairs has drafted a revised version of the Law on the National Naadam Festival (hereinafter referred to as the “draft law”). ”(Hereinafter referred to as the“ methodology ”) in the following steps:1. Selection of indicators;
2. To determine the impact assessment part of the draft law;
3. Evaluate the effectiveness of the project according to the pre-selected criteria;
4. Evaluate results and make recommendations.

The Center for Economics and Business Law (CEBL), established in 2020, is a research unit affiliated to National University of Mongolia.  The purpose of the CEBL is to make contribution to development of Mongolian Economic law and business law. 

To make comprehensive textbook, our approach will be: 
Study of current legislation on Competition and its main specifics; 
Study of problems and issues from the time of adoption of first Competition law, amendments and their impact on enforcement of law; 
Theoretical and practical approach to all subject of competition law and define their application problems; 
Review court cases related to application of administrative acts for breach of Competition law; 
Review and make analysis to fact and problem based situations on implementations of competition law, comments from business entities and open hearings; 
A critical and contextual approach, addressing the wider economic and practical realities of competition law 
An easy-to-follow writing style, including detailed explanations on specific regulations and provisions of Competition law and if necessary will include formulas and pictures.

As with many emerging markets, Mongolian insurance market have its own challenges and in this paper we surveyed prospects of this market and recommended potential ways to solve them based on current market situation and main indicators. In conclusion, Mongolian insurance market has:
-	Lopsided composition: Non-life insurance GWP accounts for 99.0% and the life insurance GWP accounts for 1% only)
-	Low loss ratio: In recent years, the loss ratio (paid loss to GWP) ranges from 20% to 50% thus it suggests that there is room to develop insurance service as well as improving claims paying level. It is also observed that the data quality should be improved;
-	Low penetration: Penetration rate of 0.5% means that insurance industry has lot to do and there are lots of business space which is not insured;
-	Where the amount of value at risk in overall economy and available capital of insurance market which is to receive risks transferred from economy is not comparable, trying to halt reinsurance premium flow from local economy to overseas countries are like trying to stop flood water. Reinsurance premium flows to market where there is capacity. Instead, it might be preferable for FRC to take steps to attract investment to local insurance market. Increased capacity means decreased reinsurance demand;

